<TITLE> PM leaves for Saudi Arabia Monday night </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 19 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will leave for Saudi Arabia late Monday to discuss bilateral issues on the first foreign trip since she took oath on Jan 6. Foreign minister Dipu Moni will accompany her on the four-day visit to the kingdom. They are expected to discuss welfare of Bangladeshi workers in Saudi Arabia. Foreign ministry officials have said Hasina will meet King Abdullah bin Abdullah Aziz Al Saud on April 21. The prime minister will fly at 11.45pm Monday on a Bangladesh Biman flight and return home on April 25.
